Using set notation, the given assertion can be written as: $$B=\{b_{1}, b_{2}, ..., b_{n}\},\] $$ $$F=\{f_{1}, f_{2}, ..., f_{m}\},\] $$ $$R=\{r_{1}, r_{2}, ..., r_{k}\},$$ and $$Q=\{q_{1}, q_{2}, ..., q_{l}\},$$ where $b_i$ and $f_j$ are members of the set $B$ and $F$ respectively, and $r_k$ and $q_l$ are members of the set $R$ and $Q$ respectively.

$$

\dfrac{B \subseteq F}{R \cap Q} \\[2em]

$$

B \subseteq F
